Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Put the @couscous{120%g} in a #bowl{}.

Pour in the @boiled water{240%ml} for the couscous, stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, then cover tightly with #cling film{}. Leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Pop the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} into a #medium bowl{} with the garlic, @cornflour{20%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Toss to coat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the chicken to the pan and season with @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Heat another large frying pan on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every couple of mins - this will result in the courgette picking up some nice colour.

Once cooked, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks) and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the lime zest, chopped mint and @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove it from the heat. Add the @fresh chilli jam{25%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce to the pan and stir to coat.

Stir through the charred courgette until coated in the glaze. Remove from the heat.

Add a squeeze of lime juice, then taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{}, then stir through the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}. Share between your bowls.

Top with the glazed chicken and courgette.

Finish with a dollop of zesty mint yoghurt and serve any remaining lime wedges on the side.

Enjoy!